.claude/
/target
**/target
# sdk/ uses `target-dir = "../../../build/examples"` for MIPS builds.
# Everything under /build/examples is noise EXCEPT the final .exe
# binaries — those we commit so a fresh clone has runnable SDK
# examples without needing nightly + build-std installed. The exes
# are small (<10 KiB each, <25 KiB for the whole set) and rebuilding
# them is deterministic, so re-committing when they change is
# cheap. Git-ignore can't re-include a path under an ignored parent,
# so we use directory-level wildcards instead of a single `/build`
# rule: everything under /build/examples/mipsel-sony-psx/release/
# is ignored except `.exe` files.
/build/examples/**/deps/
/build/examples/**/incremental/
/build/examples/**/build/
/build/examples/**/*.d
/build/examples/**/*.rlib
/build/examples/**/*.rmeta
/build/examples/**/*.timestamp
/build/examples/**/.cargo-lock
/build/examples/**/.fingerprint/
/build/examples/**/.rustc_info.json
/build/examples/**/.package-cache
/build/examples/**/CACHEDIR.TAG
Cargo.lock.orig
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/

# Local bios/game files — never commit
bios/
roms/
discs/

# Source-image assets for texture cooking. Small cooked PSXT blobs
# live in sibling `assets/` directories and ARE committed; raw
# JPG/PNG sources are typically 5-20 MB each and would balloon the
# repo size. Devs re-cooking textures drop the source into vendor/
# locally — `make assets` cooks only when the source file is
# present, so fresh clones build cleanly against the committed
# `.psxt` blobs without needing to redownload anything.
#
# Small sources (OBJ meshes, shader source) stay committed — they're
# KB-range and reproducibility of the cook matters there.
/sdk/examples/*/vendor/*.jpg
/sdk/examples/*/vendor/*.jpeg
/sdk/examples/*/vendor/*.png
/sdk/examples/*/vendor/*.bmp

# Run artifacts
run/
traces/
goldens/*.bin
goldens/*.raw
/build/examples/**/.cargo-build-lock
